<l:h1>1908 - Trouble in the Balkans:<l:/h1>
Four nations were watching the Balkans and waiting for the opportunity to conquer land and to influence the Turkish empire. That opportunity came in 1908, when there was a revolution in Turkey that resulted in a new and more democratic constitution. Bulgaria declared its independence and Crete used the opportunity to join with Greece. Emperor <l:ep_franz_joseph> of Austria-Hungary had the largest advantage, taking over both Bosnia and Herzegovina. [<l:ww1_pre1914_bosherz>]
<l:h1>1912 - The first Balkan War:<l:/h1>
The Serbian, Montenegran, Bulgarian and Greek kings joined in the Balkan alliance. They declared war on Turkey, which lasted for fifty days. Turkey lost and the land in the Balkans was divided between the four kings.
<l:h1>1913 - The second Balkan war:<l:/h1>
Bulgaria had an ambition to expand and attacked Serbia. But the Serbian army of 200,000 soldiers beat the Bulgarian army of 300,000 soldiers, and more than 50,000 Bulgarian soldiers lost their lives.
