<l:h1>1914, June - The murder in Sarajevo:<l:/h1>
On the 22nd of May, 1911m ten young officers formed a secret organisation called "The Black Hand" in the Serbian capital Beograd. Their goal was to reunite the Balkan areas in one state: Yugoslavia. In June 1914, three members of "The Black Hand" were sent to Sarajevo to murder Archduke Franz Ferdinand, heir of the Austria-Hungarian empire. The murders of the Archduke and his wife gave Austria-Hungary an excuse to invade the Balkans. Austria-Hungary gave Serbia an unrealizable ultimatum, and when Serbia refused to fulfill it, the Austrian-Hungarian army invaded them. [<l:ww1_1914_ferddead>, <l:ww1_1914_austro-h>, <l:ww1_1914_russmemo>, <l:ww1_1914_serbresp>, <l:ww1_1914_a-hdecwa>]
