<l:h1>1914, July-August - From Balkan War to World War I:<l:/h1>
28. July: Serbia asks Russia for help against Austria-Hungary.
29. July: <l:ep_tsar_nikolaj> agrees to help and begins to mobilize his army.
30. July: Germany gives Russia an ultimatum demanding that the mobilization be stopped. When Russia denies, Germany declares war. The Frenchmen begin to mobilize their army. [<l:ww1_1914_germande>]
2. August: Germany uses the Schlieffen-plan: The plan was to have the German troops go through Belgium to avoid the French main front. After hopefully defeating France in 6 weeks, the German army could be transported to the eastern front. [<l:ww1_1914_germpass>, <l:ww1_1914_belgsayn>, <l:ww1_1914_greytalk>]
3. August: England had promised to defend neutral Belgium. Therefore, an ultimatum was sent to Germany demanding them to pull out of Belgium.
4. August: Germany does not answer and England declares war against Germany  - World War I. [<l:ww1_1914_theobelg>]

